# File Placement

Large files exist — do not make them worse without splitting.

## Current heavy files (think before adding 50+ lines)

| File | ~Lines | Prefer |
|------|--------|--------|
| `components/chat/ChatPage.tsx` | 1200 | New chat UI → `components/chat/` subcomponents |
| `routes/settings.tsx` | 900 | New section → extract `components/settings/` |
| `routes/customers.tsx` | 775 | Modals → `components/customers/` |
| `lib/store.tsx` | 580 | Keep actions; extract pure helpers to `lib/` if complex |

## Placement rules

| What | Where |
|------|-------|
| New route page | `src/routes/*.tsx` (TanStack file routing) |
| Reusable UI | `src/components/` (not inline 200-line JSX in routes) |
| Business logic | `src/lib/` — pure functions, no React |
| Derived data hooks | `src/hooks/` |
| Types | `src/types/index.ts` |
| Seed data | `src/data/` |
| shadcn primitives | `src/components/ui/` — do not put app logic here |

## When to extract a component

- JSX block reused 2+ times
- Modal/drawer > ~80 lines
- Route file would exceed ~400 lines after your change — extract first, then add feature

## Do not

- Create parallel state folders or `services/` layer until real API exists
- Add new top-level `src/` directories without user approval
